<subSubSection id="C93A183A94ADFE4846DC703BE2EE6A8C" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="method">
<paragraph id="6D079624C91A70757216EB005A30170B" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Method.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26C866EDEBD7DC6899252E578C586F6C" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Squash preparations were made on root tips obtained from germinating seeds. Root tips were pre-treated with 0.4% colchicine for 3 hours and then fixed in Carnoy fixative solution for 1 hour. After hydrolysis in HCl 1N at 60 °C, the tips were stained in leuco-basic fuchsine for 7-8 minutes.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8640B1EA42053A41793DAAB693D93DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="observations">
<paragraph id="DC4FC3407EA1B4773EF9CE17455541B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Observations.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4488EF8F174C56B1CDA63ADC6ABB3CEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species occurs in southern Europe, from the Iberian Peninsula to the Balkans, in Turkey, and in Syria (
<bibRefCitation id="4582F9BF0DC125DAB2EB32E69CFA1760" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="3, Edagricole, Bologna" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Greuter, W, 2006. Compositae (pro parte majore). In: Greuter W, Raab-Straube E von (Eds) Compositae. Euro+Med Plantbase - the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity. [accessed 3 December 2021] https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" title="Compositae (pro parte majore). In: Greuter W, Raab-Straube E von (Eds) Compositae. Euro + Med Plantbase - the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity. [accessed 3 December 2021]" url="https://doi.org/10.3372/wi.36.36206" year="2006">Greuter 2006</bibRefCitation>
+). Although several chromosome counts are available in the literature (
<bibRefCitation id="91EE3914A8E4749CE203A232CD915482" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" author="Moore, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="281 - 299" refId="B23" refString="Moore, RJ, Frankton, C, 1962. Cytotaxonomic studies in the tribe Cynareae (Compositae). Canadian Journal of Botany 40 (2): 281 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" title="Cytotaxonomic studies in the tribe Cynareae (Compositae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1139/b62-027" volume="40" year="1962">Moore and Frankton 1962</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E66E4E4132A7C47A52D5533267298B08" author="Chuksanova, NA" journalOrPublisher="Botanicheskii Zhurnal (Moscow and Leningrad)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="381 - 386" refId="B11" refString="Chuksanova, NA, Sveshnikova, LI, Alexandrova, TV, 1968. A new evidence on chromosome numbers in species of the family Compositae. Giseke. Botanicheskii Zhurnal (Moscow and Leningrad) 53: 381 - 386" title="A new evidence on chromosome numbers in species of the family Compositae. Giseke." volume="53" year="1968">Chuksanova et al. 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C6B0E9C28126541E3623218685D8F199" author="Valdes, B" journalOrPublisher="Boletin de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural, Seccion Biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="193 - 197" refId="B31" refString="Valdes, B, 1970. Numeros cromosomicos de algunas plantas espanolas. Boletin de la Sociedad Espanola de Historia Natural, Seccion Biologica 68: 193 - 197" title="Numeros cromosomicos de algunas plantas espanolas." volume="68" year="1970">Valdes 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F779CCC1D69485BED0D7F0AC2B0CB682" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" author="Kuzmanov, B" editor="Loeve, A" journalOrPublisher="Taxon 28 (4)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="391 - 408" refId="B21" refString="Kuzmanov, B, Georgieva, S, Nikolova, M, 1979. Reports. In: Loeve, A, Ed., IOPB chromosome numbers reports LXIV. Taxon 28(4): 391 - 408, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" title="Reports." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/j.1996-8175.1979.tb00530.x" volumeTitle="IOPB chromosome numbers reports LXIV." year="1979">Kuzmanova et al. 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="639619A03DB2166968765575FBD79DF9" author="Snogerup, S" editor="Kamari, G" journalOrPublisher="Flora Mediterranea" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="331 - 337" refId="B28" refString="Snogerup, S, 1995. Reports 491-517. In: Kamari, G, Felber, F, Garbari, F, Eds., Mediterranean chromosome number reports 5. Flora Mediterranea 5: 331 - 337" title="Reports 491 - 517." volume="5" volumeTitle="Mediterranean chromosome number reports 5." year="1995">Snogerup 1995</bibRefCitation>
), no data have been published so far for Italy, where two subspecies can be found, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="33C7B6C2CCA7AE4628FF226060D2A590" authority="subsp. illyricum" genus="O." lsidName="O. illyricum subsp. illyricum" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="subSpecies" species="illyricum" subSpecies="illyricum">O. illyricum subsp. illyricum</taxonomicName>
, distributed throughout south-central Italy (including Sardegna and Sicilia), and 
<taxonomicName id="56BC435EA931DDBD70843D0DFD883E5D" genus="O." lsidName="O. illyricum subsp. cardunculus" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="subSpecies" species="illyricum" subSpecies="cardunculus">O. illyricum subsp. cardunculus</taxonomicName>
(Boiss.) 
<normalizedToken id="98976B9FCB06AEF4DAC3D7879DC1E46D" originalValue="Arènes">Arenes</normalizedToken>
, which is known only for Sicilia (
<bibRefCitation id="961BFAA224C574FFF721FF39D1FD90D8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" author="Bartolucci, F" journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="179 - 303" refId="B5" refString="Bartolucci, F, Peruzzi, L, Galasso, G, Albano, A, Alessandrini, A, Ardenghi, NMG, Astuti, G, Bacchetta, G, Ballelli, S, Banfi, E, Barberis, G, Bernardo, L, Bouvet, D, Bovio, M, Cecchi, L, Di Pietro, R, Domina, G, Fascetti, S, Fenu, G, Festi, F, Foggi, B, Gallo, L, Gottschlich, G, Gubellini, L, Iamonico, D, Iberite, M, Jimenez-Mejias, P, Lattanzi, E, Marchetti, D, Martinetto, E, Masin, RR, Medagli, P, Passalacqua, NG, Peccenini, S, Pennesi, R, Pierini, B, Poldini, L, Prosser, F, Raimondo, FM, Roma-Marzio, F, Rosati, L, Santangelo, A, Scoppola, A, Scortegagna, S, Selvaggi, A, Selvi, F, Soldano, A, Stinca, A, Wagensommer, RP, Wilhalm, T, Conti, F, 2018. An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy. Plant Biosystems 152 (2): 179 - 303, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" title="An updated checklist of the vascular flora native to Italy." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/11263504.2017.1419996" volume="152" year="2018">Bartolucci et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). We confirm here the chromosome number 2 
<emphasis id="3A5EAEF184FEE06099D938ADB1EE82B5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">n</emphasis>
= 34 previously reported for the species.
</paragraph>
